TITLE: Resource-Specific Lifecycle Callbacks Organization
DESCRIPTION: Example of organizing resource-specific lifecycle callbacks in separate files and importing them into the main data provider.
SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/withLifecycleCallbacks.md#2025-04-20_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
// in src/posts/index.js
export const postLifecycleCallbacks = {
    resource: 'posts',
    beforeDelete: async (params, dataProvider) => {
        // delete all comments related to the post
        // first, fetch the comments
        const { data: comments } = await dataProvider.getList('comments', {
            filter: { post_id: params.id },
            pagination: { page: 1, perPage: 1000 },
            sort: { field: 'id', order: 'DESC' },
        });
        // then, delete them
        await dataProvider.deleteMany('comments', { ids: comments.map(comment => comment.id) });

        return params;
    },
};
```

