TITLE: Implementing Unselect Functionality with useUnselect Hook in React-Admin
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the useUnselect hook to create an unselect button in a react-admin application. It imports necessary hooks, retrieves the current resource and selected IDs, and defines a click handler to unselect the selected records.
SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useUnselect.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useListContext, useUnselect } from 'react-admin';

const UnselectButton = () => {
    const { resource, selectedIds } = useListContext();
    const unselect = useUnselect(resource);

    const handleClick = () => {
        unselect(selectedIds);
    };

    return (
        <button onClick={handleClick}>
            {`Unselect ${selectedIds.length} records`}
        </button>
    );
};
```

